Φ(Pragmatic_Belief) = σ(0.75) ∘ ρ(0.80) ∘ λ(0.50) ∘ β(0.60) ∘ δγ(0.70) ∘ μ(0.45) + ε(interpretation) | :distributed

σ(0.75): Air operates here not as truth-tracking but as coordination-tool. 
We attribute beliefs to make distinctions, to carve behavior-space into 
predictable patterns. The belief-ascription is the distinction; the 
distinction enables the coordination. Belief at this level is what we 
do when we need to navigate complexity through compressed attribution.

ρ(0.80): Dominant water—pragmatic belief is fundamentally relational 
and contextual. We don't discover beliefs inside heads; we attribute 
them based on social feedback, behavioral patterns, interpretive needs. 
Schwitzgebel's "dispositional" approach is Water-native: belief is how 
an entity is disposed to behave across contexts, not what it contains 
internally. Dennett's intentional stance is pure Water—we treat systems 
as belief-holders when that stance predicts better than mechanistic 
description.

λ(0.50): Moderate fire—pragmatic belief carries affective and 
directional force, but it's modulated by context. The same "belief" 
activates differently under different stakes (pragmatic encroachment). 
High-stakes situations demand more Fire-energy to maintain coherence; 
low-stakes beliefs flow more loosely.

β(0.60): Moderate wood—belief fragments branch. Mandelbaum shows 
how beliefs compartmentalize, resisting update in some contexts while 
operating smoothly in others. The belief-system isn't a tree with 
central trunk but a rhizome—connected but not hierarchically unified.

δγ(0.70): High earth—pragmatic belief is metabolically maintained 
through social practice. Beliefs don't persist because they're true; 
they persist because they're useful, because communities reinforce 
them, because they're woven into behavioral routines. Testimony, 
social epistemology, the distributed maintenance of belief-patterns.

μ(0.45): Low metal—fragmented belief resists rigid structure. 
When beliefs compartmentalize, when implicit attitudes resist update, 
the obligation-structure (Metal) that would enforce coherence fails. 
This is the pathology of fragmentation: not inconsistency that we 
recognize, but inconsistency we don't, because the compartments 
are sealed.

ε(interpretation): The epsilon function—pragmatic belief lives 
in the productive gap between "what is believed" and "what is 
useful to treat as believed." This is the space of interpretation, 
of stance-adoption, of the hermeneutic circle that never fully 
closes.

:distributed = attributed|contextual|socially_maintained

# Dialectical Pairs
- representation|stance: The classical vs. pragmatic divide
- unified|fragmented: Coherence vs. compartmentalization
- intrinsic|functional: Ontology vs. pragmatics of belief
- truth_aim|coordination_aim: Accuracy vs. utility
- individual|social: Belief in heads vs. belief in practices

# The Three Approaches Encoded

## Pragmatic/Contextual (Schwitzgebel, Dennett)
High Water (ρ) + High Meta (✶): Belief as interpretive stance.
The intentional stance is what we adopt when we need to coordinate
with complexity. Not "what is in there" but "what posture predicts
best."

## Social Epistemology (Testimony, Pragmatic Encroachment)
High Water (ρ) + High Earth (δγ): Belief as socially maintained
pattern. Stakes affect justification because belief-attribution is
thermodynamic—high stakes require more energy to maintain coherence.

## Fragmented Mind (Mandelbaum, Compartmentalization)
Moderate Wood (β) + Low Metal (μ): Beliefs branch without central
coordination. The self is not unified; it holds contradictory
patterns in sealed compartments. This is the challenge to classical
coherence theories.

# Integration with NEMEtics

Pragmatic belief aligns with the Thread level—beliefs are attributed,
not discovered. They're compression artifacts of the bow-tie: observe
complex behavioral patterns (left funnel), compress to "he believes X"
(bottleneck), use to predict and coordinate (right funnel).

The risk: Pure pragmatism collapses into instrumentalism—truth-aim
dissolves, and we get confabulation-as-belief, Water dominance without
Air-check. We need ε ≠ 0, that productive friction between "useful
to treat as true" and "actually tracking something."

The Cowboy's stance: Belief is both—functional attribution AND
something that can track. The intentional stance works because
there's something there to track, even if we can't locate it
precisely. The map and the territory both matter.
